        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-06-18T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-06-18T01:00:00-05:00" n="1054" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1054">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.48/6–1847: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-06-18T15:00:00+09:00">June 18, 1947—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 18—4:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1324. Embassy has now received from Foreign Office detailed requests for
                    post-UNRRA relief along lines described Embassy’s telegram <pb facs="1328" n="1318" xml:id="pg_1318"/> 1274 [<hi rend="italic">1275</hi>], June 12, 11
                    a.m., together with request third meeting Sino–U. S. working group be held June
                    20 to discuss them.</p>
                <p>Embassy expressed unwillingness to discuss request (copies being airmailed<note n="39" xml:id="d1054fn1">Despatch No. 817, June 18, not printed.</note>)
                    without opportunity to inspect them closely and agreed meeting be held June 23.
                    Accordingly Embassy should receive Department’s instructions, especially with
                    reference Embassy’s telegram 1184, May 31, 1 p.m.; Consulate General’s telegram
                    Shanghai 1325, June 1, 1 p.m.;<note n="40" xml:id="d1054fn2">Telegram No. 1325
                        not printed.</note> Embassy’s telegram 1275, June 12, 11 a.m., and Embassy’s
                    telegram 1276, June 12, noon, to be despatched by urgent telegram from
                    Washington not later than Friday<note n="41" xml:id="d1054fn3">June 20.</note>
                    p.m. Washington time.</p>
                <p>Highly desirable that clear cut statements of policy and plan for future
                    operation of post-UNRRA relief be given Chinese now.</p>
                <p>Sent Department, repeated Shanghai 548.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
